{"post-27242": {"user": "Ralf Valgard, the White Wolf", "user_num": 451, "timestamp": "1457195440000", "message": "I'm just gonna drop this here.\u00a0 If you are interested in it, or want to criticize aspects of it, just post here.A good while ago I had a board game called HeroScape.\u00a0 I won't go into to much detail, but it was interesting table-top war game featuring a cast of characters and squads that did battle on custom battlegrounds.\u00a0 I've always liked the idea, and was having fun with some ideas, thinking of TFS.AttributesVitality - A measure of your life force; once this reaches 0, your character is incapacitated.Strength - When your character makes a melee attack, this value is added to your overall attack value.Dexterity - When your character makes a ranged attack, this value is added to your overall attack value.Intelligence - When your character makes a magical attack, this value is added to your overall attack value.Defense - When your character is defending against an opponent, this value is added to your overall defense value.Skills and AbilitiesSome characters have special skills and abilities.\u00a0 For example:Quick Fire:\u00a0 You may attack twice in a single turn.Magical Defense:\u00a0 When being attacked by a magical character, add +10 to your defense.Heal:\u00a0 Roll the d20; add this value to your Intelligence; heal a target character for this amount.Flying:\u00a0 A flying character cannot be engaged by melee characters, and while flying has +10 Defense.EquipmentEach character will have equipment.\u00a0 Weapons, armor, items, etc.\u00a0 Some equipment, like a sword, might increase your attack values; other items, like shields, might increase your defense values.\u00a0 Specific charms might increase total magic damage, vitality, etc.\u00a0 Some armor, like heavy armor, might greatly increase your defense.CombatEngagement RulesA character with range, like someone armed with a bow or who can cast spells, is considered' ranged'; they do not need to 'Engage'.\u00a0 However, a character who wishes to make a melee attack must first spend a turn to 'Engage' their target.\u00a0 The opponent can waste a turn to 'retreat', or decide to just engage in melee as well, in which case they must spend a turn to 'engage' too.\u00a0 Sometimes, you might not be able to engage another character because another character might be 'blocking your way' or something.\u00a0 Also, if you are engaged and attempt to flee, then you will take a penalty (the attacker rolls for attack; the value is deducted from your vitality; you cannot defend against this).AttackingWhen you attack, you roll the d20.\u00a0 Take that value and add your STR/DEX/INT (depending on the time of attack).\u00a0 Additionally, add any bonuses you may have from abilities, and also any bonuses from worn equipment.\u00a0 The defender then rolls the d20; he adds his Defense value, as well as his own bonuses from abilities and equipment, and compares it to the attacker's total value.\u00a0 If the defender's total value is higher, he has successfully defended against the attack.\u00a0 If the attacker's was higher, the attack was successful; subtract the defender's value from your attack value; that is the amount of damage that was dealt.", "link_list": [], "image_list": [], "html": "I'm just gonna drop this here.\u00a0 If you are interested in it, or want to criticize aspects of it, just post here."}, "post-27245": {"user": "Renner", "user_num": 1141, "timestamp": "1457196942000", "message": "How would you implement a fair dice rolling system on the forum?", "link_list": [], "image_list": [], "html": "How would you implement a fair dice rolling system on the forum?"}, "post-27246": {"user": "Garo Zelsai", "user_num": 33, "timestamp": "1457197961000", "message": "This would be cool for an individual scene or thread, maybe a preplanned battle thread or something.", "link_list": [], "image_list": [], "html": "This would be cool for an individual scene or thread, 